  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chicken breast and cook until browned on both sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion and cook until softened, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the pork belly and cook until browned, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the rice and stir to coat with oil, about 2 minutes.",
    "Add the chicken stock cube, water, fish sauce, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and cover, simmering for 18 minutes or until the liquid has been absorbed.",
    "Fluff the pilaf with a fork and stir in the cream, until well combined.",
    "Season to taste with salt and pepper, if needed.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped green onions or chilies, if desired."
  ],
